What if you loose state file ?
If we loose the state file then terraform doesn't know that any infra exists so it will create new resources again if we ran terraform apply.
So we have to add IMPORT Block in our configuration file to map those existing infrastructure resources. Previously we use : 
"$ terraform import aws_instance.web i-1234567890abcdef0" cli command.

Understanding terraofrm drift : 
When state file no longer matches real world configuration is called a Drift.
when we run $terraform plan , it will show us something is changed. we have two choices: we can accept or revert.
If we have to accept then we have to run the command : $terraform apply -refresh-only  
i.e will change state file same as resources.
Now we have to change our configuration files manually so that when we run again it should match the current state

I've detected STATE DRIFT : how to fix it ?
terraform plan -refresh-only
terraform apply -refresh-only
