MANAGING MULTIPLE ENVIRONMENTS 
Creating multiple directories : this gives problem of code duplication
dev account : mian.tf , provider.tf local file : terraform.tfstate
qa account : main.tf , provider.tf terraform.tfstate
            or 
USE terraform WORKSPACEs  : a workspace is a named container for a separate instance of your terraform state.
------------------------
same code configuration across all env.
each workspace maintains its own isolated state.
no code duplication or manual syncing required.
terraform automatically creates a workspace by the name "default" when you run "terraform init".

When u create additional workspaces, terraform creates a terraform.tfstate.d/ directory.
Each workspace get its own subdirectory with an isolated state file.
The default workspace state remain in the root directory.

Creating and Switching Workspaces : 
------------------------------------
terraform workspace 
list - list all workspace
new - create a new workspace
select - change the selected namespace
show - Display the current workspace
delete  - delete the specified workspace

